cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for medical image diagnosis, specifically for diagnosing multiple sclerosis (MS) using conventional magnetic resonance imaging (MRI). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of layer-wise relevance propagation (LRP) for uncovering relevant image features also falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of MRI data and advanced MRI markers in MS suggests a potential overlap with the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning for medical imaging also falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
